args: La la laaa... Oh, 'tis the season for love—\nand I sense another wonderful meeting\non the horizon today!
Has something happened, Orion?\nYou seem unusually happy.
Come to think of it, what happened to\nchanging how you approach women?
You looked pleased—albeit injured—\nwhen you returned from your\nescort job the other day.
Did something happen during that job?\nOr have you simply given up on change?
I've not given up on changing my approach\nat all. I have merely established the way\nmost suited to my particular person.
I would be happy to show you, if you like.\nCome, let us hurry into town!
I wasn't expecting you to drag us along\non this little adventure.
Seriously! I left half a ham back there!\nWhat are we doing here anyhow?
I think we're about to find out.
Look! Orion is speaking with someone!
You most certainly can—for when you\npassed, I knew we were fated to meet!
I cannot bear for this to be the last time\nwe ever lay eyes upon each other.
Might you join me for some tea?
A shame—but I am happy nonetheless!
I was able to honestly convey my feelings,\nand THAT is what matters. I pray you also\nlive a life equally full of self-honesty.
Um, thanks? I'm going to...go now.
I thought you were going to stop acting\non impulse. I saw no evidence of such\na thing in that absurd display.
You moved in immediately, and were shot\ndown just as fast. And yet...you look\nunusually happy.
Are you over becoming depressed\nwhenever you are rejected?
YES! You see, all of this has taught me\nthat holding back simply isn't who I am.
So that's why I will keep going up and\nspeaking to women as I did before—\nif anything, I will do it MORE!
But that means that your chances of\nrejection are going to INCREASE.
And I can live with that. From now on,\nI'm going to do what feels RIGHT.
If it doesn't work out, I can live with that!
Holding back on doing what feels right\nand regretting it is much more painful\nthan any mere rejection.
I feel like this entire adventure has ended\nup right back where it started.
'Cept he's even MORE sure of himself.
Hang on, everyone. It sounds like Orion\nput a lot of thought into this decision.
He seems a lot happier for it, too.\nThis feels like a good outcome.
Ha ha! I see spending time with me has\ngiven you a better understanding of love.
Speaking of which, aren't you ready for\nan honest romance of your own?
Huh? Well, I... I mean, it's a bit early\nfor me to be thinking about such things.
HOW DARE YOU, SIR! His Highness is\nfar above such frivolous nonsense!
It would hardly do to have our leader\ninviting literally every woman he sees\nout for a cup of tea.
Although he already invites everyone he\nmeets to stay at the freakin' castle...
You're all so overprotective towards him!\nDo not worry, {player_name}.
Pay no heed to what the others say.\nOur hearts know what is best.
Don't worry, Orion. I'm going to keep\ndoing what I feel to be right.
Well said! ...Oh, but if you ever DO\nneed advice on romantic matters,\nI'll happily lend you an ear.
You tried to help me with my love life—\nit's only fair to return the favor!
